FT  05 NOV 93 / Arenson Group founder dies
ARCHY ARENSON, founder and former chairman of Arenson Group, the office
furnishing concern, has died aged 67.
Mr Arenson began making domestic furniture in London just after the second
world war. In the 1960s, the company switched to office furniture and went
public in 1970. It was taken over in an agreed bid by Skandinavisk Holding
of Denmark in 1988. Mr Arenson had stayed on as a non-executive director.
